{"type":"message","id":"5afcc413","parentId":"2209ea24","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:20:36.937Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l08t2ipjjaf4_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 151918\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. **Completed this session**: Architecture cross-analysis, gap-decay synthesis, CFI compression experiment showing CFI alone gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n2. **Key finding**: Constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information content\r\n3. **Next experiment pending**: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending experiment is clearly defined:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test whether this distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n- Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, actionable next step. I should implement this experiment. Let me think about how to structure this:\r\n\r\n1. I need to run the same pulse data through this new hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Compare results against the binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5, freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n3. Document the findings\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create a script or run the analysis. Let me look at what files exist that I could build on.\r\n\r\nFrom the context, there was a `pulse_2026-03-24 151819.md` as the last pulse, and there's `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` documenting the previous experiment.\r\n\r\nThe most specific, actionable next step is to implement the hybrid scoring experiment. I should create a Python script to run this analysis or modify an existing analysis script.\r\n\r\nLet me create a script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Applies the hybrid scoring formula\r\n3. Compares against binary thresholds\r\n4. Outputs the comparison results\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression experiment revealed constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) as metaprogramming contamination that binary thresholds struggle to filter. The hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should naturally suppress these by downweighting high-frequency tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate Python script to run hybrid scoring experiment, comparing against binary thresholds on the same 200-pulse dataset, testing whether CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nCompares: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) vs binary thresholds\r\nTests on same 200-pulse dataset from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data (from CFI compression experiment)\r\n# Expected: list of {'text': str, 'pulse_id': str, 'is_research': bool}\r\n# is_research: True = research/problem-solving pulses, False = routine/task pulses\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_tokens(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract all tokens with their CFI and frequency metrics.\"\"\"\r\n    token_data = defaultdict(lambda: {'pulses': [], 'cfs': [], 'count': 0})\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        tokens_in_pulse = set()\r\n        for token in pulse['text'].split():\r\n            if token not in tokens_in_pulse:\r\n                token_data[token]['pulses'].append(pulse['pulse_id'])\r\n                token_data[token]['cfs'].append(1.0)  # Placeholder\r\n                token_data[token]['count'] += 1\r\n            tokens_in_pulse.add(token)\r\n    \r\n    return token_data\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi(token_data):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute CFI = consistency across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    cfi_data = {}\r\n    for token, data in token_data.items():\r\n        total_pulses = len(data['pulses'])\r\n        unique_pulses = len(set(data['pulses']))\r\n        cfi_data[token] = unique_pulses / total_pulses if total_pulses > 0 else 0\r\n    return cfi_data\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq, cap=120):\r\n    \"\"\"score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/cap)\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / cap)\r\n\r\ndef binary_filter(token, cfi, freq, cfi_thresh=0.5, freq_low=3, freq_high=120):\r\n    \"\"\"Original 3D binary filter.\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi >= cfi_thresh and freq_low <= freq < freq_high\r\n\r\n# Load data and compute metrics\r\n# [DATA_LOADING_BLOCK - integrate with existing pulse corpus]\r\n\r\n# Compare filtering strategies\r\nprint(\"=== HYBRID SCORING vs BINARY THRESHOLDS ===\")\r\nprint(\"\\nToken Categories:\")\r\nprint(\"  - Constant format: freq≈160, CFI=1.0 (metaprogramming artifacts)\")\r\nprint(\"  - Research trajectory: freq<120, CFI>0.5 (causal tokens)\")\r\nprint(\"\\nBinary filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\")\r\nprint(\"Hybrid score: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\")\r\nprint(\"\\nExpected: Hybrid suppresses constant-format (160/120=1.33 capped to 1.0)\")\r\nprint(\"          But constant-format CFI=1 × 1.0 = 1.0 still scores HIGH\")\r\nprint(\"          NEEDS refinement: freq^0\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:19:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380036934}}
