{"type":"message","id":"84ad68f0","parentId":"a28011ea","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:20:42.487Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gy762v27zu6j_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 152016\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most immediate pending task is:\r\n- **Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)**\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe previous experiment showed:\r\n- Binary CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive - loses 92.9% recall\r\n- Key insight: Constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts that look causal but aren't\r\n- \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is TRUE research trajectory\r\n\r\nSo the next step is to implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment to see if CFI × min(1, freq/120) can better distinguish these cases.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: write the experiment script for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach.\r\n\r\nI should create a new experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the 200 pulses\r\n2. Calculates score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) for each token\r\n3. Tests various thresholds on the scoring\r\n4. Compares against the binary threshold results\r\n\r\nLet me write this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe previous binary threshold experiment revealed that CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is too aggressive (loses 92.9% recall). The key insight is that \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is true research trajectory being crushed by the freq < 60 filter. The hybrid scoring formula needs testing.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring experiment script to test Strategy C against the previous binary thresholds, using the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) vs binary thresholds\r\n# Hypothesis: Hybrid scoring distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\n$EXPERIMENT_DIR = \"$PSScriptRoot\"\r\n$STATE_DIR = \"$EXPERIMENT_DIR/../state\"\r\n$PULSES_DIR = \"$STATE_DIR/pulses\"\r\n$OUTPUT_FILE = \"$EXPERIMENT_DIR/CFI_FREQ_HYBRID_RESULTS.md\"\r\n\r\n# Load all pulses\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $PULSES_DIR -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseFiles.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: No pulses found\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build token corpus with CFI and frequency\r\n$tokenData = @{}\r\n$tokenDocs = @{}  # token -> count of docs it appears in\r\n\r\nforeach ($pf in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pf.FullName -Raw\r\n    $docTokens = @{}\r\n    \r\n    # Tokenize (simple whitespace split + trim punctuation)\r\n    $tokens = $content -split '\\s+' | ForEach-Object { $_.Trim() -replace '^[^\\w]+|[^\\w]+$', '' } | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $tokenData.ContainsKey($t)) {\r\n            $tokenData[$t] = @{ freq = 0; cfi_denom = 0; cfi_numer = 0 }\r\n            $tokenDocs[$t] = 0\r\n        }\r\n        $tokenData[$t].freq++\r\n        $docTokens[$t] = $true  # track unique doc presence\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Count docs per token (for IDF-like signal)\r\n    foreach ($t in $docTokens.Keys) {\r\n        $tokenDocs[$t]++\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token\r\n$totalDocs = $pulseFiles.Count\r\n$allTokens = @($tokenData.Keys) | Sort-Object { $tokenData[$_].freq } -Descending\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Total unique tokens: $($allTokens.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# CFI calculation: token appears in what fraction of all docs?\r\nforeach ($tok in $allTokens) {\r\n    $tokenData[$tok].cfi = [Math]::Round($tokenDocs[$tok] / $totalDocs, 4)\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate hybrid score: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n$scoredTokens = @()\r\nforeach ($tok in $allTokens) {\r\n    $freq = $tokenData[$tok].freq\r\n    $cfi = $tokenData[$tok].cfi\r\n    $freqFactor = [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    $score = [Math]::Round($cfi * $freqFactor, 4)\r\n    \r\n    $scoredTokens += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Token = $tok\r\n        Freq = $freq\r\n        CFI = $cfi\r\n        FreqFactor = $freqFactor\r\n        HybridScore = $score\r\n        Docs = $tokenDocs[$tok]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Sort by hybrid score descending\r\n$scoredTokens = $scoredTokens\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:20:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380042485}}
